{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_70","type":"agent_message","text":"The pattern is clearer now: the native run is getting past one host-class reference at a time, and the next blocker is `clojure.lang.RT` itself. That strongly suggests Clojure bootstrap needs reflection metadata for a small set of `clojure.lang.*` host classes used from `core.clj`, not just isolated one-offs. I’m extracting those direct host-class references so I can add a tighter grouped fix instead of chasing them one by one for many more cycles."}}
